TASK_DESCRIPTION=Add violation_bump_counter() helper to .claude/hooks/common.sh. Wake-state ledger /tmp/doey/<session>/wait-state-<pane_safe>.json. Reset signal: .claude/hooks/on-pre-tool-use.sh writes sentinel at ${RUNTIME_DIR}/status/<pane>.tool_used_this_turn (NOT on-prompt-submit — that fires on every wake-delivered turn). Logic: mkdir lock with stale-lock mtime recovery, DOEY_ENFORCE_VIOLATIONS on/shadow/off short-circuit, sentinel check, window-expiry at 120s, counter bump on same-reason zero-tool wake, warn at 3, breaker at 5 (latched via breaker_tripped), next_wake_earliest=now+30 NO blocking sleep, owner nudge (Boss if Taskmaster, else Taskmaster). Sanitize last_wake_reason via tr -cd A-Z_. Call helper from taskmaster-wait.sh AND reviewer-wait.sh at top (reason-agnostic). Standalone commit. Plan Phase 4.
